    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <head>No. 559.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoffman</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 17, 1880</date>.
                            (Received June 5.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 208.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 205, in relation
                        to the case of Henry Pinkos, an American citizen and an Israelite, I have
                        the honor to inform you that I am at length in receipt of a note from Mr. de
                        Giers, in answer to mine of the 20th April.</p>
                <p>The Russian Government grants to Pinkos a delay of three months in order to
                        wind up his business.</p>
                <p>On sending to notify him I found that he was still at St Petersburg, the
                        police superintendent of his district having permitted him to remain from
                        day to day since the expiration of the time allowed him by General Zouroff
                        to await the answer of the Russian Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WICKHAM HOFFMAN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
